!***************************************************************
!Chemical network and cooling/heating for POPSICLE simulations
!Author: Piyush Sharda (Leiden) 2024
!Contact: sharda@strw.leidenuniv.nl
!
!This is a simple one-zone collapse test following
!the chemical and thermal evolution of a primordial cloud.
!The dynamics is described by the Larson-Penston-type
!similar solution and includes cooling and heating processes.
!
!Reactions taken from primordial_wD network, Omukai 2000, 2005,
!Glover & Jappsen 2007, Glover et al. 2010
!For details on cooling/heating, look at the KROME paper.
!
!This is for prestellar collapse only, includes cosmic ray chemistry
!as well as photo chemistry
!
!This test uses Semenov+2003 opacities, and does not use KROME's inbuilt dust
!functionality to do dust (except for freezeout reactions)
!***************************************************************
!
!Simply make the test from the KROME home directory via
!>>./krome -t popsicle_semenov_photo_cr
!>>cd build
!>>make
!>>./test
!
!The test will output a file called fort.22
!which can be read in your favorite programming language
!to plot stuff
!
